_:N4c6306fb321f4479ad233c0080200bdd <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"summary\">Summary</h2>\n\n<p>The Flood Forecasting Centre (<abbr title=\"Flood Forecasting Centre\">FFC</abbr>) provides forecasts, data and information to support flood response in England and Wales for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the UK and Welsh governments</li>\n  <li>Category 1 and 2 responders</li>\n  <li>the wider responder community</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We continuously improve our services through:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>our development programme - bringing science and research into use</li>\n  <li>working closely with our users - to understand their evolving needs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"our-services\">Our services</h2>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/flood-forecasting-centre-services-flood-guidance-statement/flood-guidance-statement-user-guide\">Flood Guidance Statement</a> (<abbr title=\"Flood Guidance Statement\">FGS</abbr>) is:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>a 5-day flood risk forecast at a local authority scale</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>issued daily</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>for strategic, tactical and operational planning decisions</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/flood-forecasting-centre-services-rapid-flood-guidance/rapid-flood-guidance-information-and-user-guide\">Rapid Flood Guidance</a> (<abbr title=\"Rapid Flood Guidance\">RFG</abbr>) is:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>a summer service - providing short notice updates to supplement the <abbr title=\"Flood Guidance Statement\">FGS</abbr></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>issued on days with heightened flood risk</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>for supporting decision making in the 0 to 3 hour timescale</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/flood-forecasting-centre-services-flood-outlook/flood-outlook-information-and-user-guide\">Flood Outlook</a> is:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>a guidance forecast - showing flood likelihood for the coming month</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>issued twice a month</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>for supporting decision making in the 6 to 30 day timescale</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We also provide:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>an <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://api.foursources.metoffice.gov.uk/docs/flood-guidance-statement-api-public.html\">Application Programming Interface (<abbr title=\"Application Programming Interface \">API</abbr>) for the <abbr title=\"Flood Guidance Statement\">FGS</abbr></a>  - available for developers</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>specialist hydrometeorological services for the Environment Agency and Natural Resources Wales</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"development-programme\">Development programme</h2>\n\n<p>As well as our services, we work to improve the national capability in flood forecasting.</p>\n\n<p>We do this by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>bringing new science and forecasting techniques into operational use</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>developing our services to provide more accurate, targeted information</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"user-research-and-engagement\">User research and engagement</h2>\n\n<p>We continually improve our services to ensure they meet user needs.</p>\n\n<p>We do this by: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>measuring our performance through regular user feedback</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>undertaking research to inform service improvements</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>keeping engaged with our users - for example through <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/flood-forecasting-centre-services-training-and-user-engagement/flood-forecasting-centre-training-and-engagement\">open days and our user group</a></p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"flood-alerts-and-warnings-for-your-area\">Flood alerts and warnings for your area</h2>\n\n<p>The Environment Agency issues <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://check-for-flooding.service.gov.uk/start-page\">flood alerts and warnings in England</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Natural Resources Wales issues <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://naturalresources.wales/flooding/check-flood-warnings/?lang=en\">flood alerts and warnings in Wales</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The Scottish Environment Protection Agency issues <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://floodline.sepa.org.uk/floodupdates/\">flood alerts and warnings in Scotland</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The Met Office issues <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/weather/warnings-and-advice/uk-warnings#?date=2020-06-02\">weather warnings for the UK</a>.</p>\n\n</div>" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
